Repro steps:
1. Enable Smart lock for a user on the device;
2. Add an kiosk app;
3. Launch kiosk app manually from login screen;
4. Try Ctrl+/Ctrl- zoom accelerators in kiosk session

At step 4, the zoom accelerators are not working.

This is because the platform app's accelerators are stored in a static variable and intialized when the first platform app window is created. Smart lock has a hidden window created before the kiosk session starts and causing the kiosk specific accelrators are not registered. 

We have DCHECK but unforunately this only happens on device where Smart lock app is avaialble and DCHECK is not enabled there.

Code for painting SVGImage, in draw(), does this:

        view-&gt;updateLayoutAndStyleForPainting();
        view-&gt;paint(paintContext, enclosingIntRect(srcRect));

This code is invoked during painting, when layout should not be called. Over the years it has been a source of many security bugs.

It's not a paint invalidaiton problem, I suspect, because it always lays out in the size that has already been negotiated, so paint can be invalidated for that rect before layout.

