Currently, user_story.UserStory, android.AppStory, page.Page doesn't share a same Run method. The logic of defining the exact signature of the Run methods &amp; calling them is customized in shared_user_story_state

This leads to confusion of how one about to create a new UserStory &amp; allow a chance for custom control flow, which is a feature that telemetry don't want to support (see https://docs.google.com/document/d/1WIxSYzI9V9ZYcWzIodl2dBIhTqCUKBZfxusVsUVcmlc/edit#heading=h.winu2uy6fsjl for more details).

We need to create a same Run method for all subclass of user_story. The signature of that run method is:

class UserStory:
   def Run(self, shared_user_store_state_instance):
      ...

class Page(UserStory):
   def Run(self, shared_user_store_state_instance):
      assert isinstance(shared_user_store_state_instance, SharedPageState)
      runner = action_runner.ActionRunner(shared_user_store_state_instance.current_tab)
      ...
      self.RunPageInteractions(runner)


Page tests that want to access more than the action runner can create a new subclass of shared_page_state that exposes other fields, e.g: android_action_runner,...

